    ### Usage
    Here is an example of the mixin producing a car icon on a `<div class="icon car"></div>` in use:

    ~~~scss
    .icon {
      &:before {
        @extend %icon-font-base;
      }
      &.car {
        @include icon-font($car);
      }
    }

    // We apply the font-base rules to a class of "icon" and
    // the mixin adds the pseudo-element's content value.
    // The above produces the following css:

    .icon.car:before {
      content: "\f1b9";
    }
    .icon:before {
      display: inline-block;
      font-family: FontAwesome;
      font-style: normal;
      font-weight: normal;
      line-height: 1;
      -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
      -moz-osx-font-smoothing: grayscale;
    }
    ~~~
